= Quicksilver Say

== DESCRIPTION:

Quicksilver Say is a plugin for the popular Quicksilver application launcher that provides an interface for the OS X text-to-speech `say` command. This plugin can be used to invoke `say` from Quicksilver, providing an alternative to the terminal.

== INSTALL:

Download Xcode project and build from source, or download Say Plugin.qsplugin.zip, uncompress it, and double-click Say Plugin.qsplugin to install.

== USAGE:

Select an application from Quicksilver, or enter any string of text, tab over to the secondary menu, and select "Say it!" to hear the string read by your default text-to-speech voice, changeable in VoiceOver Utility.

== SOURCE:

The source code for Quicksilver Say is available at http://github.com/dancavallaro/quicksilver-say/tree/master

